## 7. Event-Driven Feedback (not timer polling)

Prefer attaching `EventHandler` to component status controls over timer-based polling:

```lua
-- ✅ Event-driven — fires only when state actually changes
if comp["ledSystemPower"] then
    comp["ledSystemPower"].EventHandler = function(ctl)
        debugPrint("System power → " .. (ctl.Boolean and "ON" or "OFF") .. " (Source: Room Controls)")
        updatePowerFeedback()
    end
    debugPrint("Registered: system power handler")
end

-- ❌ Timer polling — runs on a schedule regardless of change
local timer = Timer.New()
timer.EventHandler = function() updatePowerFeedback() end
timer:Start(1.0)
```

Use a timer **only** when hardware cannot notify on change (true polling requirement with no available status control).

